{{Quote|The Fourth Great Schism, which occurred a millennium ago, brought on a thousand years of fighting, the ascendance of Darth Ruin and the Sith, and the plague that provided the drumbeat for what was truly the Republic's Dark Age. It was a military campaign that nearly brought an end to civilization.|Restelly Quist's writings|<ref name="The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref>}}
The '''Fourth Great Schism''' was a [[Great Schism/Legends|pivotal split]] among the ranks of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] in [[2000 BBY/Legends|2000 BBY]].<ref name="TEA" />

Around this time, a [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] known as [[Darth Ruin/Legends|Phanius]] had abandoned the [[Jedi Code/Legends|ways of the Jedi]] in pursuit of alternate teachings, leading him on a quest to revive the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark-side]]-worshipping [[Sith/Legends|Sith Order]]. By this point, the Sith were commonly believed to have been destroyed for [[Standard century/Legends|centuries]]. The [[Dark Jedi/Legends|fallen]] Jedi Master proved otherwise, however, after seeking out a number of existing [[Sith cult/Legends|Sith clans]] throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].<ref name="JVS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> Assuming leadership over these clans, Phanius declared himself a [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] under the identity of [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Ruin.<ref name="END">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref>

Prompted by the Dark Lord's ascension, fifty additional [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] followed in Ruin's footsteps, leaving the Jedi Order in favor of his growing Sith empire. These events gave rise to the [[New Sith]], initiating a [[Millennium/Legends|thousand-year]]-long crusade—the [[New Sith Wars]]—against the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the Jedi.<ref name="TEA" />

